snippet.textDisplay:
Fun fact - If you actually look into it, theres almost zero consequences to not having insurance in a minor collision. Lady hit me on the highway in heavy traffic. Very minor damage. I dont know why, but the officer didnt notice that her insurance was expired. Her insurance company did not want to file a claim due to the fact that it was not valid and she was technically no longer a customer as of like 3 days or so. So I did some research and found out that the only way to have her pay for the damages is to take her to court. There are essentially 2 phases to this. If the judge deems it in my favor and orders her to compensate me, she has to pay. But if she does not, I have to go back to court and waste more of my time and have to pay more in lawyer fees, just to get the judge to order to garnish her wages. Even still, if her income is too low then the case basically gets thrown out anyway. Should also mention I live in illinois.

Please tell me if I'm wrong. Would like to know if it were to happen again. Thank you.
